Package agent

Class TableData

java.lang.Object
agent.TableData
public class TableData extends Object
The TableData class provides methods for retrieving distinct transactions, distinct column values, and aggregate column values from a database table.

    • getAggregateColumnValue

      public Object getAggregateColumnValue(String table, TableSchema.Column column, QUERY_TYPE aggregate) throws SQLException, NoValueException
      This function retrieves the minimum or maximum value of a specified column in a given table using a SQL query and returns it as a double.
      Parameters:
      table - The name of the table in the database from which to obtain the data.
      column - The column for which the aggregate value is being calculated.
      aggregate - an enum type QUERY_TYPE that specifies the type of aggregate function to be used (either MIN or MAX)
      Returns:
      the value of the aggregate column specified by the input parameters.
      Throws:
      SQLException
      NoValueException
